title: PTI-P candidate Arbab Muhammad Wasim Khan wins PK-73
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf Parliamentarian (PTI-P) candidate Arbab Muhammad Wasim Khan won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-73 Peshawar-II by securing 21,949 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ullema-e-Islam (JUI) candidate Abdul Haseeb who bagged 14,752 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained at 39.61 per cent.
